image.altText: A shirtless, muscular man lifts a bucket of water.

props.synopsis: The residents of Rainbow Lodge have committed multiple crimes and been in and out of prison for decades. For many, its program is their last chance to take responsibility for their actions and prove they're ready for the outside world – but one slip-up could land them back inside.

title.children: Meet the residents of Rainbow Lodge, the broken men with nowhere else to go

image.altText: woman standing in window smiling

props.synopsis: An ageing generation of single women who have raised children, and are often well-educated with careers and middle-class backgrounds, are becoming permanent residents of caravan parks amid the housing crisis.

title.children: Most of the residents at this caravan park in regional Victoria are single women aged over 55

image.altText: Kysaiah Pickett handballs to his right during a 2024 AFL match.

props.synopsis: Melbourne will finish round 12 inside the top four if it can defeat Fremantle in Alice Springs, while Essendon faces a challenge in getting past the improved Gold Coast Suns. Follow live.

title.children: Demons out to reclaim top-four spot against Dockers

image.altText: A close up image of Josh Frydenberg looking serious.

props.synopsis: The former federal treasurer is considering running for his old seat of Kooyong, but would need to displace pre-selected candidate Amelia Hamer to do so.

title.children: Josh Frydenberg is considering running in Kooyong again, where a young woman has already been chosen to run

image.altText: A graphic showing four Ozempic pens, three of which have the brand name ripped out

props.synopsis: Yet again, the manufacturers of a wildly popular drug, taken by millions of women globally, have not collected data on what this drug might do to a woman's reproductive organs or offspring.

title.children: Ozempic 'oops babies' should make women think twice about weight loss drugs

image.altText: WHALAN HOME GAS EXPLOSION

title.children: 'Confronting scene' as one person missing after house explosion in Sydney

image.altText: butterflies seen pinned to a black background.

props.synopsis: In early 1947, the Melbourne Museum discovered the loss of more than 800 specimens of rare Australian butterflies. When other museums reported similar thefts, the trail led to a former champion skier trying to cope with a crumbling marriage.

title.children: A former ski champion visited multiple museums — and walked out with hundreds of dead butterflies

image.altText: A police wagon parked on the street outside a block of flats.

props.synopsis: A man has been arrested after the death of a woman in Darwin's northern suburbs, with Northern Territory police confirming they are treating the incident as an "alleged domestic violence death".

title.children: Man arrested after woman's body found in Darwin flat, in what police claim is 'alleged domestic violence death'

image.altText: house damage

props.synopsis: A cold front causes major damage to buildings in southern WA, with reports of another tornado in Bunbury.

title.children: Powerful storm takes roof off hotel, damages properties in south west WA

image.altText: A row of guns lined up in a collector's home.

props.synopsis: A family and domestic violence complaint will automatically strip firearms owners of their guns under tough new gun laws being introduced by the WA Government in the wake of the Floreat shooting murders.

title.children: WA gun owners accused of domestic violence to lose weapons in wake of Floreat shooting murders

image.altText: A defence force plan dropping goods from its cargo hold.

image.altText: a photo of a man and two searchers

props.synopsis: Matthew, 34, was last seen in Newlyn, north-east of Ballarat, on Friday afternoon. His family is concerned about his welfare due to a medical condition.

title.children: SES searches forest north of Ballarat for missing man

image.altText: Em Rusciano in yellow and black houndstooth jacket over yellow top, with ornate jewelled earrings

props.synopsis: Em Rusciano burst onto the national stage as an advocate for ADHD women. But when she asked a doctor to investigate autism, it was a flat-out no. Ahead of a national tour, she shares the reality of being a late-diagnosed neurodivergent, perimenopausal woman.

title.children: Em Rusciano discovered her ADHD and autism in her 40s. Then came perimenopause

image.altText: Two women hold a bucket between them as they walk along a South Korean island followed by a woman in a cart.;

props.synopsis: After a bombardment of shells in January, residents on the South Korean island of Yeongpyeong are anxiously waiting for another attack. Some wonder: could it happen again?

title.children: 'North Korea won't give in': Living in the shadow of a giant, this island is building bunkers

image.altText: Kid

props.synopsis: Alex de Minaur puts a call out to find a kid in the French Open crowd who stuck with him during the Australian's stunning victory.

title.children: 'He gave me life': De Minaur hugs kid in the crowd who stuck with him through French Open marathon

image.altText: woman poses for pictures at a lookout

props.synopsis: For those who choose to live in student housing, rents for a single room can often be more than the price of a whole apartment, with some international students saying the prices are "insane".

image.altText: A heater on the floor with two feet warming up next to it. The feet have socks on

title.children: How much does it cost to run an aircon versus portable electric heater in winter? Here's which appliance saves you more

image.altText: A large spacecraft in between four large telephone poles.

title.children: China lands spacecraft on far side of Moon

image.altText: The sun sets over the chimneys of an oil refinery

image.altText: A person in a white protective suit stands next to a lake holding a dead crane.

image.altText: Tom Gleeson standing with his arms crossed with a serious look on his face with th Hard quiz logo in the top left corner

props.synopsis: Oh, you're back? Something to prove after last week's effort? Let's see what you've got.

image.altText: A pan of one pot spaghetti with parsley, capers, tuna, lemon, peas and asparagus, illustrating our recipe.

props.synopsis: Olive oil has become a lot more expensive, which might have you rethinking how you cook. Make use of the other oils in your pantry with these easy dinner recipes.

image.altText: Stephen hugging his two daughters Chloe and Jess.

props.synopsis: Despite moving to Australia as a child and raising his whole family here, a criminal conviction over methamphetamine means Stephen is facing deportation to a country where he has no ties.

image.altText: Penny Squibb

image.altText: A young Papua New Guinea man wearing a black hoodie and sunglasses looks sombrely out over a large pile of rocks.

image.altText: a young man riding a horse bucking up in a suburban street

image.altText: Large white mansion.

title.children: If you've ever been tempted to handle a dead snake, read this first

title.children: Tedesco set to play in Origin opener as scans reveal extent of Edwards's injury

props.synopsis: In Mexico, an untold number of women are murdered, kidnapped, or subjected to unspeakable violence at the hands of men. These are just some of their stories. WARNING: Some readers might find details in this story distressing.
